   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource.required_quantity"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource.required_quantity">
<p>
The required quantity of the required resource. 
</p>
<note number="1">Quantity can be specified using amount, duration etc.</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_action_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_action_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_action_relationship">
<p>A relationship between an action and a required resource. The required resource could be related to many different types of actions such as:
<lu>
<li>the task, task step, activity, etc that requires the resource</li>
<li>activities such as calibration, purchases, etc, that's needed prior to using the resource</li>
</lu>
</p>
<p>The role of the relationship is determined by classification.</p>
<note number="1">
The relationship between an action and the required resource can be classified as "Required_by", "Requires", etc.
</note>
</ext_description>
